onship name   Vial  , and there has also been some confusion with   Vail   and   Vale  .","nickname for a docile, calf-like person, from Middle English <i>vel(e)</i>, <i>veille</i>, <i>fel(e)</i> ‘calf; veal’, Old French <i>veel</i> ‘calf’."]}]},{"name":"Robert","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["One of the many French names of Germanic origin that were introduced into Britain by the Normans; it has since remained in continuous use. It is derived from the nearly synonymous elements <i>hrōd</i> ‘fame’ + <i>berht</i> ‘bright, famous’, and had a native Old English predecessor of similar form (<i>Hreodbeorht</i>), which was supplanted by the Norman name. Two dukes of Normandy in the 11th century bore the name: the father of  William the Conqueror  (sometimes identified with the legendary Robert the Devil), and his eldest son. It was borne also by three kings of Scotland, notably  Robert the Bruce  (  1274–1329 ), who freed Scotland from English domination. The altered short form <i>Bob</i> is very common, but <i>Hob</i> and <i>Dob</i>, which were common in the Middle Ages and gave rise to surnames, are extinct.  See also  Rupert ."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705189,"age":24,"year":"1259","julianDay":2180901,"title":"100 Years of Conflict Between England and France Ends","description":"Treaty of Paris was signed on December 4, 1259, which ended 100 years of conflict between England and France.","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Treaty_of_Paris_(1259)","urlTitle":"Wikipedia - Treaty of Paris 1259","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705190,"age":55,"year":"1290","julianDay":2192224,"title":"Jews Expelled From England","description":"After years of anti-Semitic behavior, King Edward I expelled Jews from England in 1290.","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"When Robert Veel was born in 1235, in Tortworth, Gloucestershire, England, his father, Robert la Veyle, was 28 and his mother, Honor le Velle, was 28. He married Hawise Gore in 1258, in Tortworth, Gloucestershire, England. They were the parents of at least 1 son. He died in 1302, in Gloucestershire, England, at the age of 67."},"et":{"1235–1302":"1235–1302","1239–1301":"1239–1301","1264–1343":"1264–1343","1207–1253":"1207–1253","1207–Female":"1207–Surnud","1239":"1239","before 1235":"enne 1235","1259":"1259","1258":"1258","1302":"1302","1235":"1235","1301":"1301","1343":"1343","1253":"1253","1264":"1264","1290":"1290","1207":"1207","Tortworth, Gloucestershire, England":"Tortworth, Gloucestershire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Gloucestershire, England":"Gloucestershire, England"},"fi":{"1235–1302":"1235–1302","1239–1301":"1239–1301","1264–1343":"1264–1343","1207–1253":"1207–1253","1207–Female":"1207–Kuollut","1239":"1239","before 1235":"ennen vuotta 1235","1259":"1259","1258":"1258","1302":"1302","1235":"1235","1301":"1301","1343":"1343","1253":"1253","1264":"1264","1290":"1290","1207":"1207","Tortworth, Gloucestershire, England":"Tortworth, Gloucestershire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Gloucestershire, England":"Gloucestershire, England"},"fr":{"1235–1302":"1235–1302","1239–1301":"1239–1301","1264–1343":"1264–1343","1207–1253":"1207–1253","1207–Female":"1207–Décédée","1239":"1239","before 1235":"avant 1235","1259":"1259","1258":"1258","1302":"1302","1235":"1235","1301":"1301","1343":"1343","1253":"1253","1264":"1264","1290":"1290","1207":"1207","Tortworth, Gloucestershire, England":"Tortworth, Gloucestershire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","Gloucestershire, England":"Gloucestershire, Angleterre","lifeSummary":"Lorsque Robert Veel est né en 1235, à Tortworth, Gloucestershire, Angleterre, son père, Robert la Veyle, avait 28 ans et sa mère, Honor le Velle, avait 28 ans. Il a épousé Hawise Gore en 1258, à Tortworth, Gloucestershire, Angleterre. Ils ont eu au moins 1 fils. Il est décédé en 1302, à Gloucestershire, Angleterre, à l’âge de 67 ans."},"de":{"1235–1302":"1235–1302","1239–13